The paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which is a common concern in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. The proposed defense mechanism involves the use of regularized latent space based generative models, which are commonly used in the field of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of security and privacy, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for improving the performance of deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
